				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">New Young Bards<a name="63358"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 21 04 1:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I always do this with all my toons.
<br />

<br />
Level 0-2
<br />
First hunt in the new zone that dungon you get put into when creating a new toon. i hasve both done it and denied it and seems you get an easy 2 levels just for going threw the proceedure.
<br />

<br />
then get out.
<br />

<br />
Level 2-4 or 5
<br />
I usally hunt in West freeport eveil or good i bind myself up to pok so that way you are only 1 zone away. hunt here and kill rats, skellys and other yard junk.
<br />

<br />
Level 5-17 back end of Paladul Caverns
<br />
This is on the val shire side of PC. hunt bugs til 14 then hunt either owlbears til 17. get duel weild then off to the front end of pc.
<br />

<br />
Level 17-24 or 25
<br />
The front end of PC. get your a$ in a bandit group and stay there til 24 or 25.
<br />

<br />
Level 24 - 29
<br />
What i did was go to Warsilk Woods
<br />
(Giant Fort) hunt giants til 28 or 29
<br />

<br />
Level 28, 29 - 35
<br />
Hunt the skyfire ramp in OT. Get in a good group and exp really fly's.
<br />

<br />
Level 35 - 38
<br />
Hunt the tribles in DSP.
<br />

<br />
Level 38 - 42
<br />
Solo in OT.
<br />

<br />
Level 42 - 48 
<br />
Either solo or group in DL
<br />
at 46 i would start to solo because you can drop these guys like flies.
<br />

<br />
that is it for me because i am only 43</span></td>
